1 design, construction drawings, and station location. If the Red Line extends to
2 the Town of Mooresville, the Authority shall also solicit input from that Town.
3 (4) The Authority shall reimburse the City of Charlotte for the acquisition of the
4 Norfolk Southern O-Line and related property. The amount to be reimbursed
5 may not be more than the cost to the City of Charlotte to acquire the property
6 from Norfolk Southern, including any costs for indebtedness incurred by the
7 City with respect to the acquisition. The Authority and the City of Charlotte
8 shall jointly agree to a schedule for reimbursement of these costs.
9 SECTION 4.10. Repeal of Tax. – The Mecklenburg County Board of
10 Commissioners may by resolution repeal the levy and imposition of the tax in the County as
11 provided in G.S. 105-473(c). The Board of Commissioners, upon adoption of a repeal resolution,
12 shall cause a certified copy of the resolution to be delivered immediately to the Secretary of
13 Revenue. No liability for any tax levied under this Part that attached prior to the effective date
14 on which a levy is repealed shall be discharged as a result of such repeal, and no right to a refund
15 of tax or otherwise that accrued prior to the effective date on which a levy is repealed shall be
16 denied as a result of such repeal. If a county repeals a tax levied under this Part, the Authority or
17 a municipality may refinance previously issued bonds, notes, or other financing that are secured
18 or payable by receipts for the tax revenue under this Part to reduce debt service as allowed under
19 the law so long as the refinancing does not extend the date of maturity for the previously issued
20 bonds, notes, or other financing. No repeal of taxes levied and imposed under this Part shall be
21 effective until the latest of the following:
22 (1) The end of the fiscal year in which the repeal resolution was adopted.
23 (2) The date by which all previously issued or, as provided in this section,
24 refinanced, bonds, notes, or other financing obtained by the Authority or a
25 municipality secured or payable by receipts from the tax levied under this Part
26 have been satisfied.
27 (3) The date by which the Authority has fully reimbursed the City for the purchase
28 of the O-Line as required by Section 4.9(4) of this act.
29 SECTION 4.11. Study. – If a referendum held pursuant to this Part fails, then within
30 one year after the failed referendum the Charlotte Area Transit System shall develop and publish
31 a comprehensive, long-term public transportation plan that specifically includes frequent, express
32 public transportation connections between the center of the City of Charlotte and Charlotte
33 Douglas International Airport.
