13 of this subsection.
14 (d) Members of the board of trustees shall have demonstrated experience or qualifications
15 in the areas of law, finance, engineering, public transportation, urban planning, logistics,
16 government, architecture, or economic development.
17 (e) Members of the board of trustees shall reside within the territorial jurisdiction of the
18 authority as defined by G.S. 160A-904.
19 (f) Every two years, the board of trustees shall elect from its membership a group of
20 officers, which shall include a chairperson, vice-chairperson, secretary, and treasurer. An election
21 of an officer must be by a majority vote at a meeting where a quorum is present.
22 (g) No trustee may serve for more than two consecutive terms on the board of trustees,
23 but a person who has been a member for two consecutive terms may be reappointed after being
24 off the board of trustees for a period of at least two years. An initial term that is two years or less
25 shall not be counted in determining the limitation on consecutive terms. This limitation applies
26 regardless of whether the appointments are made by the same appointing authority.
27 "§ 160A-906. Expansion of authority.
28 Upon approval of authorizing resolutions by the board of trustees and the board of
29 commissioners of the affected county, the territorial jurisdiction and service area of an authority
30 may be expanded to include a whole county within this State that is contiguous to the then
31 existing territorial jurisdiction of the authority. Each of the authorizing resolutions must receive
32 an affirmative vote equal to at least seventy-five percent (75%) of the membership of the
33 applicable board. The authorizing resolutions shall contain provisions with respect to the
34 following:
35 (1) The date on which the territorial jurisdiction is to be expanded to include the
36 county.
37 (2) The extent to which the composition of the board of trustees may be amended,
38 if at all, due to the addition of the county to the territorial jurisdiction of the
39 authority. The authorizing resolutions shall not eliminate or amend the
40 requirements with respect to appointments to the board of trustees that are
41 provided in G.S. 160A-905. Subsections (b) through (g) of G.S. 160A-905
42 shall apply to any additional appointments to the board of trustees.
43 (3) Financial, legal, or operational commitments with respect to the county that is
44 to be added to the territorial jurisdiction of the authority.
45 (4) Any other matter determined to be relevant by the board of trustees and the
46 board of commissioners of the affected county.
47 "§ 160A-907. Voting; removal.
48 (a) A majority of the board of trustees constitutes a quorum for the transaction of
49 business. Each member shall have one vote.
50 (b) Each member of the board of trustees may be removed with or without cause by the
51 appointing authority.
