5 "§ 160A-908. Advisory committees.
6 The board of trustees may provide for the selection of such advisory committees as it may
7 find appropriate, which may or may not include members of the board of trustees.
8 "§ 160A-909. Purpose of the authority.
9 The purpose of the authority shall be to finance, provide, operate, and maintain for a safe,
10 clean, reliable, adequate, convenient, energy efficient, economically, and environmentally sound
11 public transportation system for the service area of the authority through the granting of
12 franchises, ownership, and leasing of terminals, buses, and other transportation facilities and
13 equipment, and otherwise through the exercise of the powers and duties conferred upon it, in
14 order to enhance mobility in the region and encourage sound growth patterns. Such a service,
15 facility, or function shall be financed, provided, operated, or maintained in the service area of the
16 authority either in addition to or to a greater or lesser extent than services, facilities, or functions
17 are financed, provided, operated, or maintained for the entirety of the respective units of local
18 government. An authority may take direct action to accomplish these purposes or may enter
19 agreements with another unit of local government in the service area of the authority or a private
20 entity to accomplish these purposes.
21 "§ 160A-910. Service area of the authority.
22 The service area of the authority shall be as determined by the board of trustees consistent
23 with its purpose but shall not exceed the sum of the following:
24 (1) The territorial jurisdiction of the authority.
25 (2) An area outside of the territorial jurisdiction of the authority provided that one
26 of the following conditions is satisfied:
27 a. If the area is within this State, the governing bodies of the political
28 subdivisions to which service is to be extended approved by majority
29 vote of their governing boards the extension of service into the
30 political subdivision or the purchase of real property within the
31 political subdivision for the extension of service.
32 b. If the area is in another state, the extension of service is approved by
33 any applicable federal or State agency and in accordance with the other
34 state's laws.
35 "§ 160A-911. General powers of the authority.
36 The general powers of the authority include all of the following:
37 (1) To sue and be sued.
38 (2) To have a seal.
39 (3) To make rules and regulations, not inconsistent with this Article, for its
40 organization and internal management.
41 (4) To employ persons deemed necessary to carry out the functions and duties
42 assigned to them by the authority and to fix their compensation, within the
43 limit of available funds.
44 (5) With the approval of the unit of local government's chief administrative
45 official, to use officers, employees, agents, and facilities of the unit of local
46 government for such purposes and upon such terms as may be mutually
47 agreeable.
48 (6) To retain and employ counsel, auditors, engineers, and private consultants on
49 an annual salary, contract basis, or otherwise for rendering professional or
50 technical services and advice.
