10 "§ 160A-924. Reports to the General Assembly.
11 The authority shall annually submit to the General Assembly, on or before February 1, its
12 annual operating report, including a report of its administrative expenditures, and its audited
13 financial report. In odd-numbered years, the report shall be submitted to the Senate and House
14 Transportation Committees. In even-numbered years, the report shall be submitted to the Joint
15 Legislative Transportation Oversight Committee.
16 "§ 160A-925. Limitations on rail transportation liability.
17 (a) As used in this section:
18 (1) Claim. – A claim, action, suit, or request for damages, whether compensatory,
19 punitive, or otherwise, made by any person or entity against:
20 a. The authority, a railroad, or an operating rights railroad; or
21 b. An officer, director, trustee, employee, parent, subsidiary, or affiliated
22 corporation as defined in G.S. 105-130.2, or agent of the authority, a
23 railroad, or an operating rights railroad.
24 (2) Operating rights railroad. – A railroad corporation or railroad company that,
25 prior to January 1, 2001, was granted operating rights by a State-Owned
26 Railroad Company or operated over the property of a State-Owned Railroad
27 Company under a claim of right over or adjacent to facilities used by or on
28 behalf of the authority.
29 (3) Passenger rail services. – The transportation of rail passengers by or on behalf
30 of the authority and all services performed by a railroad pursuant to a contract
31 with the authority in connection with the transportation of rail passengers,
32 including, but not limited to, the operation of trains; the use of right-of-way,
33 trackage, public or private roadway and rail crossings, equipment, or station
34 areas or appurtenant facilities; the design, construction, reconstruction,
35 operation, or maintenance of rail-related equipment, tracks, and any
36 appurtenant facilities; or the provision of access rights over or adjacent to lines
37 owned by the authority or a railroad, or otherwise occupied by the authority
38 or a railroad, pursuant to charter grant, fee simple deed, lease, easement,
39 license, trackage rights, or other form of ownership or authorized use.
40 (4) Railroad. – A railroad corporation or railroad company, including a
41 State-Owned Railroad Company as defined in G.S. 124-11, that has entered
42 into any contracts or operating agreements of any kind with the authority
43 concerning passenger rail services.
44 (b) Contracts Allocating Financial Responsibility Authorized. – The authority may
45 contract with any railroad to allocate financial responsibility for passenger rail services claims,
46 including, but not limited to, the execution of indemnity agreements, notwithstanding any other
47 statutory, common law, public policy, or other prohibition against same, and regardless of the
48 nature of the claim or the conduct giving rise to such claim.
49 (c) Insurance Required. –
50 (1) If the authority enters into any contract authorized by subsection (b) of this
51 section, the contract shall require the authority to secure and maintain, upon
