1 and after the commencement of the operation of trains by or on behalf of the
2 authority, a liability insurance policy covering the liability of the parties to the
3 contract, a State-Owned Railroad Company as defined in G.S. 124-11 that
4 owns or claims an interest in any real property subject to the contract, and any
5 operating rights railroad for all claims for property damage, personal injury,
6 bodily injury, and death arising out of or related to passenger rail services. The
7 policy shall name the parties to the contract, a State-Owned Railroad
