10 insureds and shall have policy limits of not less than two hundred million
11 dollars ($200,000,000) per single accident or incident, and may include a
12 self-insured retention in an amount of not more than five million dollars
13 ($5,000,000).
14 (2) If the authority does not enter into any contract authorized by subsection (b)
15 of this section, upon and after the commencement of the operation of trains by
16 or on behalf of the authority, the authority shall secure and maintain a liability
17 insurance policy, with policy limits and a self-insured retention consistent
18 with subdivision (1) of this subsection, for all claims for property damage,
19 personal injury, bodily injury, and death arising out of or related to passenger
20 rail services.
21 (d) Liability Limit. – The aggregate liability of the authority, the parties to the contract
22 or contracts authorized by subsection (b) of this section, a State-Owned Railroad Company as
23 defined in G.S. 124-11, and any operating rights railroad for all claims arising from a single
24 accident or incident related to passenger rail services for property damage, personal injury, bodily
25 injury, and death, is limited to two hundred million dollars ($200,000,000) per single accident or
26 incident or to any proceeds available under any insurance policy secured pursuant to subsection
27 (c) of this section, whichever is greater.
28 (e) Effect on Other Laws. – This section shall not affect the damages that may be
29 recovered under the Federal Employers' Liability Act, 45 U.S.C. § 51, et seq., (1908); or under
30 Article 1 of Chapter 97 of the General Statutes.
31 "§ 160A-926. Civil liability.
32 Except as provided in G.S. 160A-925, the authority shall be deemed a city for purposes of
33 civil liability pursuant to G.S. 160A-485. Governmental immunity of the authority is waived to
34 a minimum of twenty million dollars ($20,000,000) per single accident or incident. The authority
35 shall maintain a minimum of twenty million dollars ($20,000,000) per single accident or incident
36 of liability insurance. Participation in a local government risk pool pursuant to Article 23 of
37 Chapter 58 of the General Statutes shall be deemed to be the purchase of insurance for the purpose
38 of this section."
