40 PART VI. REQUIREMENTS IF MECKLENBURG COUNTY CREATES A
41 METROPOLITAN PUBLIC TRANSPORTATION AUTHORITY
42 SECTION 6.1. If Mecklenburg County creates a metropolitan public transportation
43 authority under Article 34 of Chapter 160A of the General Statutes, as enacted by Part V of this
44 act, then that Authority is subject to all the provisions of this Part.
45 SECTION 6.2. The Authority shall conduct a study of the issues listed in this section.
46 The Authority may use any source of funding available to it to conduct the studies required by
47 this section. This specifically includes funds provided to the Authority by another unit of
48 government and funds that the Authority receives as a donation or grant from any other public or
49 private source. The Authority shall complete the study required under this section and publish a
50 report no later than January 1, 2026. The Authority shall publish the report and submit copies of
51 the report to the President Pro Tempore of the Senate, the Speaker of the House of
