46 that the Authority may be substituted for the City as a party to any ongoing
47 contracts, agreements, rights, responsibilities, or liabilities with respect to
48 CATS once the Authority assumes operational control of CATS.
49 (11) Complete a value engineering study with respect to the Silver Line East as a
50 light rail line. For purposes of this section, "Silver Line East" means a mass
51 transit project that includes, at a minimum, service from the center of the City
Page 20 House Bill 948-Third Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 of Charlotte through the Town of Matthews to the Levine Campus of Central
2 Piedmont Community College. The study shall include efforts to identify and,
3 if possible, procure the funding needed to establish the Silver Line East as a
4 light rail line. Potential funding options include existing public and private
5 sources and possible new or additional funding options. This study shall
6 include an evaluation of potential additional revenue sources to include, but
7 not be limited to, additional local taxes or fees not currently authorized,
8 including additional sales taxes, taxes on parking facilities, and congestion
9 taxes; municipal service districts; tax increment financing; public-private
10 partnerships; sale of naming rights; station rents; station air rights; advertising
11 revenues; sale of amenities on public transportation (such as Wi-Fi or priority
12 seating); and private donations.
13 SECTION 6.4A. The Authority is responsible for conducting or completing in a
14 timely manner all environmental and economic studies that are required by State or federal law
15 with respect to public transportation projects.
16 SECTION 6.5. If Mecklenburg County enacts a tax authorized by Part IV of this act,
17 then the Authority and the City of Charlotte shall do all of the following effective as of the date
18 the tax levied under that Part becomes effective:
19 (1) The Authority shall begin receiving the proceeds of all of the following:
20 a. Taxes levied under Part IV of this act as provided in that Part.
21 b. Taxes levied under Article 43 of Chapter 105 of the General Statutes
22 as provided in G.S. 105-507.3.
23 c. Taxes levied under Section 3.1 of S.L. 1997-417, as added by Section
24 30 of S.L. 2006-162 and amended by Section 2(h) of S.L. 2009-527,
25 and this act, as provided in that act.
26 (2) The City shall transfer control of the operational assets of CATS to the
27 Authority subject to use agreements between the City and the Authority.
28 (3) The City shall retain ownership of any assets that are pledged as security for
29 any outstanding indebtedness. Once any outstanding indebtedness is satisfied,
30 the City shall begin transferring ownership of these assets of CATS to the
31 Authority as provided in the agreements.
32 (4) The City shall begin transferring ownership of other physical assets of CATS
33 to the Authority as provided in the agreements.
34 (5) The City shall retain the thirty million dollars ($30,000,000) required fund
35 balance from the existing CATS Revenue Reserve Fund. If these reserves
36 must be used by the City to cover any debt service payments due within the
37 current fiscal year, the Authority shall provide an amount sufficient to return
38 the fund balance to the thirty million dollars ($30,000,000) required balance.
39 Once all applicable debt obligations have been satisfied, any amount
40 remaining in the Fund shall revert to the Authority.
41 (6) The Authority shall begin making payments to the City in accordance with
42 agreements between the Authority and the City for the following:
43 a. An amount to the City that is, at a minimum, sufficient to cover any
44 debt service payments due within the current fiscal year. Amounts
45 must be provided according to a schedule that ensures the funds are
46 available prior to the required payment dates.
47 b. An amount to reimburse the City for the acquisition of the Norfolk
48 Southern O-Line as provided in the agreements.
49 (7) Except as provided with specifically identified positions or individuals,
50 employees of CATS shall be transferred from the City to the Authority.
