37 The competitive proposal method of procurement is normally conducted with more than one
38 source submitting an offer or proposal. Either a fixed price or cost reimbursement type contract
39 is awarded. This method of procurement is generally used when conditions are not appropriate
40 for the use of sealed bids. If this procurement method is used, all of the following requirements
41 apply:
42 (1) Requests for proposals shall be publicized. All evaluation factors shall be
43 identified along with their relative importance.
44 (2) Proposals shall be solicited from an adequate number of qualified sources.
45 (3) RPTAs or RTAs RPTAs, RTAs, or MPTAs shall have a method in place for
46 conducting technical evaluations of proposals received and selecting
47 awardees, with the goal of promoting fairness and competition without
48 requiring strict adherence to specifications or price in determining the most
49 advantageous proposal.
50 (4) The award may be based upon initial proposals without further discussion or
51 negotiation or, in the discretion of the evaluators, discussions or negotiations
