41 PART IX. STATE FUNDING PROVISIONS
42 SECTION 9.1. It is the intent of the General Assembly not to reduce transportation
43 funding allocations for any municipality in Mecklenburg County as a result of the enactment of
44 this act or the levy of a tax under the provisions of this act. In addition, it is the intent of the
45 General Assembly not to reduce State transportation funding for State projects located in
46 Mecklenburg County as a result of the enactment of this act or the levy of a tax under the
47 provisions of this act. Without specific authorization from the General Assembly, the Department
48 of Transportation may not reduce funding for any transportation projects as a result of this act or
49 the levy of a tax pursuant to Part II, III, or IV of this act.
50 SECTION 9.2. Nothing in this section limits the ability of the City of Charlotte to
51 provide local funding for a project that (i) is eligible for State funding under G.S. 136-189.11 and
Page 26 House Bill 948-Third Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (ii) is not a highway project. The City of Charlotte may provide local funding participation for a
2 highway project eligible for funding under G.S. 136-189.11 in any amount, but notwithstanding
3 the provisions of G.S. 136-189.11(f), the Department of Transportation may not revise highway
4 project selection ratings based on local funding participation to the extent that it exceeds five
5 percent (5%) of the project cost.
